From e41adc62a500c81099c75fb0d2734ba1a5da5c51 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Jun 2025 19:16:44 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP Replace WARN_ONCE with printk in
 ieee80211_free_ack_frame

The WARN_ONCE macro was used to log a message when pending ACK frames
were detected.

Replace it with a simple printk to log the message without generating
a warning, reducing noise in the kernel logs while still providing
debug information.

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/main.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/main.c b/net/mac80211/main.c
index 37a0a49..c4f1012 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/main.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/main.c
@@ -1907,7 +1907,7 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL(ieee80211_unregister_hw);
 
 static int ieee80211_free_ack_frame(int id, void *p, void *data)
 {
-	WARN_ONCE(1, "Have pending ack frames!\n");
+	printk("Have pending ack frames!\n");
 	kfree_skb(p);
 	return 0;
 }
-- 
2.34.1

